{"id":"project-LICHEN-hhcn","title":"pending_drop_tail decrement may wrap with count underflow protection","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Lines: 300-312 (pending_drop_tail)

```c
static void pending_drop_tail(struct lichen_meshcore_adapter *adapter)
{
    if (adapter->pending_count == 0U) {
        return;  // Correctly guards against count underflow
    }

    adapter->pending_tail =
        (adapter->pending_tail + ARRAY_SIZE(adapter->pending) - 1U) %
        ARRAY_SIZE(adapter->pending);
    memset(&adapter->pending[adapter->pending_tail], 0,
           sizeof(adapter->pending[adapter->pending_tail]));
    adapter->pending_count--;
}
```

The function checks pending_count before operating, which is good. However:

1. The decrement order is: update tail, clear entry, decrement count. If an interrupt fires between tail update and count decrement, the state is inconsistent.

2. The modulo operation handles wrap correctly: if pending_tail is 0 and ARRAY_SIZE is 8, then (0 + 8 - 1) % 8 = 7. Good.

3. pending_count is uint8_t. The decrement is safe due to the > 0 guard.

